# BDD Framework: (behaviour-driven development)

Cucumber is a officially supported BDD automation tool.
In cucumber Behave is a third party tool which used in BDD framework in python
Behave is used to creating features files

1) Features contains collection of scenarios.
-> 1 features consists of Given
                          when
                          Then
     This format is called Gherkin language.

# Installation of Behave ->
1) Feature file supports only Pycharm professional edition
2) In terminal enter -> pip install behave
3) Select local interpreter



